---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import FormattedDate from '../components/FormattedDate.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import { sortByPubDateDesc } from '../utils/sort';

const recentPosts = sortByPubDateDesc(await getCollection('blog')).slice(0, 6);
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Low Hanging Data</h1>
			<p class="lead">
				Data analysis should be <strong>concise</strong>, <strong>transparent</strong>, and
				laser-focused on the <strong>low hanging fruit first</strong>.
				Before chasing complex models or elaborate dashboards, ask: what does the data already
				tell us plainly?
			</p>

			<hr />

			<h2>The Philosophy</h2>
			<p>
				Most analyses fail not because the analyst lacks skill, but because they skip straight
				to sophistication. The result is work that is hard to reproduce, hard to explain, and
				answers questions nobody asked.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Low Hanging Data</strong> is built around three commitments:
			</p>
			<ul class="principles">
				<li>
					<strong>Concise</strong> — Say what the data shows in as few words and charts as needed.
					If you can't explain the finding in one sentence, the analysis isn't done yet.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Transparent</strong> — Show your sources, your assumptions, and your limitations.
					An analysis nobody can verify is an opinion with extra steps.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Low Hanging Fruit First</strong> — Start with counts, averages, and distributions
					before reaching for machine learning. Simple questions answered clearly deliver more value
					than complex models that nobody trusts.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<hr />

			<h2>Why This Matters</h2>
			<p>
				The data field has a bias toward complexity. Practitioners are rewarded for using
				sophisticated tools and impressive jargon. Meanwhile, the most useful insights often
				come from a well-structured pivot table or a single well-chosen chart.
			</p>
			<p>
				This site exists to push back against that bias. Every article here starts with the
				simplest possible approach and only adds complexity when it's genuinely warranted.
				The bar for "complex enough" is always: does this additional complexity change a decision?
				If not, drop it.
			</p>

			<hr />

			<h2>What Low Hanging Fruit Looks Like</h2>
			<ul class="topic-grid">
				<li><strong>Counts &amp; totals</strong> — How many? How much?</li>
				<li><strong>Distributions</strong> — Where does most of the data cluster?</li>
				<li><strong>Trends over time</strong> — Is it going up, down, or flat?</li>
				<li><strong>Top &amp; bottom N</strong> — Who or what stands out?</li>
				<li><strong>Missing data</strong> — What don't we know, and does it matter?</li>
				<li><strong>Simple comparisons</strong> — Is A bigger than B?</li>
			</ul>

			<hr />

			<p>
				Browse the <a href="/article">Articles</a> for practical guides on applying these principles,
				or read more <a href="/about">about this project</a>.
			</p>

			<hr />

			<h2>Latest Articles</h2>
			<ul class="post-grid">
				{
					recentPosts.map((post) => (
						<li>
							<a href={`/article/${post.id}/`}>
								{post.data.heroImage && (
									<img src={post.data.heroImage} alt="" width={720} height={360} />
								)}
								<h4 class="post-title">{post.data.title}</h4>
								<p class="post-desc">{post.data.description}</p>
								<p class="post-date">
									<FormattedDate date={post.data.pubDate} />
								</p>
							</a>
						</li>
					))
				}
			</ul>
			<p class="view-all"><a href="/article">View all articles →</a></p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
<style>
	.lead {
		font-size: 1.1em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.principles {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
	}
	.principles li {
		padding: 0.75em 1em;
		margin-bottom: 0.75em;
		border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
		background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.5);
	}
	.topic-grid {
		columns: 2;
		column-gap: 2em;
	}
	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.topic-grid {
			columns: 1;
		}
	}
	hr {
		margin: 2em 0;
	}
	.post-grid {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
	}
	.post-grid li {
		width: calc(50% - 0.75rem);
	}
	.post-grid li a {
		display: block;
		text-decoration: none;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray-light), 1);
		border-radius: 8px;
		overflow: hidden;
		transition: box-shadow 0.2s ease;
	}
	.post-grid li a:hover {
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
	}
	.post-grid img {
		width: 100%;
		height: 160px;
		object-fit: cover;
		display: block;
	}
	.post-title {
		margin: 0.75rem 1rem 0.25rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		font-size: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}
	.post-desc {
		margin: 0 1rem 0.5rem;
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		line-height: 1.4;
	}
	.post-date {
		margin: 0 1rem 0.75rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}
	.post-grid li a:hover .post-title {
		color: rgb(var(--accent));
	}
	.view-all {
		text-align: right;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}
	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.post-grid li {
			width: 100%;
		}
	}
</style>
